nexus-badges (0.3.3) stable; urgency=low

  * Download counts are now outputted as a formatted string, this
    ensures large counts are displayed in a more readable fashion as
    shields.io does not do any formatting tricks.
  * Added new badge format 'github-html'. This format allows users to
    set separate label-colors to be displayed dependent of the browsers
    preferred color scheme.
  * Added copyright file to debian package

 -- WardLordRuby <@wardlordruby Discord>  Tue, 3 Jun 2025 13:00:00 +0000

nexus-badges (0.3.2) stable; urgency=low

  * Added additional badge that totals downloads of all tracked mods
  * Fixed lintian debian package lints
  * macOS uninstall script now removes config files for all users
  * Updated cli aliases and documentation

 -- WardLordRuby <@wardlordruby Discord>  Tue, 14 Jan 2025 02:30:00 +0000

nexus-badges (0.3.1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Overhaul to 'badges.md' output format.
  * Added new badge types for Nexus Mods (URL, rSt, AsciiDoc, HTML).
  * Added badge style customization.
  * Added deb package and purge script for linux.
  * Added pkg install and uninstall script for macOS.
  * Fixed a bug that caused the automation set state command to not work

 -- WardLordRuby <@wardlordruby Discord>  Fri, 03 Nov 2024 12:34:56 +0000